The main principle directing my choice amongst the im- mense store of such materiale placed at my disposal by the kind assistance of many eminent amateurs (whom I now thank for their essential services in furthering my object) has been to consult the interests of archaeology no less than those of fancy and the muse. With this view historic por- traits and memoriale of important events were the primary object of my researcheS, and have been introduced as exten- sively as my success permitted3 and this, indeed, has so far exceeded my first expectatione as to render my ancient por· trait gallery unusually complete. But, from the very nature of the art supplying my materiale, by far the larg-er part fall within the province of mythology, a branch of classical study on which, if critically examined‚ they throw the clearest light..
